Gallery Item 1

This piece has a dramatic, architectural abstract style. The composition is built from vertical blocks of deep teal, charcoal black, warm cream, grey and metallic gold. The surface looks textured, almost like layered plaster or heavy acrylic paint, with visible scraping, dripping and palette-knife marks.

The mood is urban, moody and sophisticated. The gold accents give it a sense of refinement, while the dark vertical forms suggest city structures, weathered walls, or an abstract skyline. It would work well in a modern gallery, corporate office, hotel lobby, or luxury interior.

Suggested title: Fragments of a Silent City
Style: Contemporary abstract expressionism
Dominant colours: Teal, black, cream, grey, gold
Feeling: Bold, elegant, atmospheric, urban

Gallery Item 2

This piece is softer and more fluid. It uses flowing organic shapes in peach, rust orange, cream, grey-blue, charcoal and subtle gold. The forms appear to move across the canvas like ink, smoke, marble, mineral veins, or geological layers. The texture gives it a tactile, polished fine-art feel.

The mood is warm, calm and natural, with a strong sense of movement. The burnt orange centre creates a focal point, while the blue-grey and cream areas balance it with coolness and space. It feels less urban than the first work and more connected to landscape, stone, water or natural erosion.

Suggested title: Erosion of Light
Style: Fluid abstract / organic abstraction
Dominant colours: Rust, peach, cream, slate blue, charcoal, gold
Feeling: Warm, flowing, balanced, natural, refined

Gallery Item 3
This artwork has a structured modern abstract style, combining soft geometry with organic curves. The composition uses large overlapping blocks and rounded forms in olive green, stone beige, cream, terracotta, charcoal and muted gold. It feels like a mix between architectural design, aged plaster, and contemporary collage.
